    "paragraph_or_text_span": "Clinical summary Information for patients Microbial keratitis is a sight-threatening bacterial or fungal infection of the cornea. Usually unilateral, it can cause moderate to severe pain, redness, potentially severe photophobia, discharge and blurred vision. The most likely cause is contact lens wear but others include corneal exposure, ocular injury and surgery. This Clinical Management Guideline",
